values.language-designer-gen-text-config-text:
# EagleView Embedded Explorer State Plane Test
### Development Viewer. Not to be shared outside of VertiGIS and EagleView.
-----

##### To launch the EagleView Embedded Explorer (E3), open the _I want to..._ menu and select **Open EagleView**.
##### E3 should open in the bottom panel, to the location of the VertiGIS Studio Web (VSW) map.

##### The two maps should stay in sync with one another. Try zooming, panning, rotating either map.  You should be able to close the component and reopen it.

##### Known Issues:
- ##### Popping-out the E3 component throws an error.
- ##### Occasionally an error was thrown when using the bearing tool in E3  to rotate the view. This may be fixed. 
- ##### If the extent of the VSW map changes programmatically (e.g. user selects a bookmark), the E3 viewer may not sync with the extent change.  

##### Please report any issues to [jon.swoveland@vertigis.com](jon.swoveland@vertigis.com)
